title: Inverleigh Nature Conservation Reserve
description:
a.k.a. as Inverleigh Flora & Fauna Reserve.
1050ha of remnant grassy woodland, 30km west of Geelong.

items.title: Chiloglottis spp.
items.content_text: I was told this is a natural hybrid between C. trapeziformis and C valida. It was growing in a colony near the little fenced-off area in the reserve.

items.title: Sherardia arvensis
items.content_text: Four petal lilac flowers are very small.

items.title: Chrysocephalum spp.
items.content_text: A single bud on the end of each stem.

items.title: Hieracium spp.
items.content_text: Yellow Hawkweed (P) — Hieracium pratense — Family: Asteraceae — Aster

items.title: Thysanotus patersonii
items.content_text: The small mauve to violet flowers , about 1cm wide, are born singly at the end of short branches on the flowering stem.

items.title: Uraba lugens
items.content_text:
Gum-Leaf Skeletoniser - Uraba lugens. (Roselia lugens).
Family Noctuidae.
